tweet: Keep in mind this was in the pre-email early-to-mid 1990s, so my vaguely humorous cover letter was sent via fax. It was a numbers game... a hustle... but in each case the hiring manager said I made them laugh enough to want to meet me...

tweet: Somehow this actually worked. I ended up with a paid internship at a publishing company one summer,  a writing gig at a computer training company the next, and before my senior year the great @cindystivers found me a job at the yet to launch @TimeOutNewYork...
